verbose_text: IRDye800-E [PEG 4 -c (RGDfK)] 2 Recently, Liu et al. further studied optical imaging of tumor integrin alphavbeta3 expression by using a near infrared fluorescent IRDye (R) 800CW labeled cyclic RGD dimer with a tetra (ethylene glycol) (PEG4) linker i.e., E [PEG4-c (RGDfK)] 2, PEG4 = 15-amino-4,7,10,13 tetraoxapentadecanoic acid) in a U87MG tumor model.
